claim.claim-text:
1. A method to start an internal combustion engine, the method comprising:
opening or maintaining open at least an intake valve of a cylinder in response to a request to start an internal combustion engine;
holding open said at least an intake valve through an exhaust or compression stroke of said cylinder;
closing said at least an intake valve during an intake or compression stroke of said cylinder;
adjusting opening timing of said at least an intake valve to a position after top-dead-center of the intake stroke of said cylinder; and
varying the opening timing of said at least an intake valve while said at least an intake valve opening time is after top-dead-center of the intake stroke of said cylinder.

22. A method to start an internal combustion engine, the method comprising:
opening at least an intake valve of a cylinder and opening a throttle from a closed position in response to a request to start an internal combustion engine, said throttle located upstream of an intake manifold;
closing said intake valve relative to the exhaust valve opening timing of a mechanically driven exhaust valve operating in said cylinder; and said intake valve at a position retarded from top-dead-center of the intake stroke of said cylinder.
